n memoirs of elite Chinese and foreign engineers, correspondence between gentry and powerful officials, travelogues of American missionaries and engineers, as well as other sources, Hornibrook offers a fascinating history of the social and political effects of industrialization in Pingxiang County.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCoal mines and miningxHistoryx19th centuryxChinaxPingxiang (Jiangxi Sheng). 0aCoal mines and miningzChinazPingxiang (Jiangxi Sheng)xHistoryy19th century. 0aIndustrializationxHistoryx19th centuryxChinaxPingxiang (Jiangxi Sheng). 0aIndustrializationzChinazPingxiang (Jiangxi Sheng)xHistoryy19th century. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Chinese Studies. 4aBusiness and Economics : Development. 4aHistory : History. 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845689840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438456898423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438456898/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles